&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agile Six is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Technical Software Architect&lt;/strong&gt; to join a cross-functional team working with the Department of Veterans Affairs on an integrated patient portal experience on &lt;a href=&quot;http://va.gov/&quot;&gt;VA.gov&lt;/a&gt;. The goal of the My HealtheVet (MHV) team is to improve Veterans’ digital experience by giving them one place to easily manage their VA health care, community care, disability benefits, and other information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will lead the evolution and maintenance of the architecture, leveraging Ruby on Rails, Git, React, React Native, JavaScript, TypeScript, Node.js, GraphQL, FHIR, HL7 and DevSecOps practices. You will balance modern software architecture patterns, legacy system integration, modularity, scalability, and accessibility while relentlessly focusing on improving Veterans&#39; experience with digital healthcare tools. You will also bring strong interpersonal, leadership, and collaboration skills to maintain an environment of effective delivery within large-scale, cross-functional agile teams, ensuring technical solutions align with user needs, accessibility, and the VA&#39;s mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this is a Key Personnel role, as stipulated by our contract, considered &quot;essential to work performance&quot;. The resumes of Key Personnel are subject to government review and approval, and any changes to Key Personnel (such as voluntary or involuntary separation) may require government oversight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Period of Performance for this contract expires on April 16, 2027. There is a strong likelihood we will continue this work under a follow-on contract beyond April 16th, but we won’t have clarity on the continuation path until closer to that date.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
